WEBVTT

00:00.167 --> 00:01.701
<i>Previously on New Amsterdam"...</i>

00:01.733 --> 00:03.608
You've been accused of form

00:03.633 --> 00:06.020
a non therapeutic alliance
with your patient, Avi Mantell.

00:06.047 --> 00:08.415
Rules exist for a reason.
And I broked them

00:08.449 --> 00:09.650
Now, the only thing for me to do

00:09.684 --> 00:12.219
is to be a different therapist.

00:12.253 --> 00:13.820
I was actually here to talk to Max

00:13.855 --> 00:15.489
about extending my leave.

00:15.523 --> 00:17.734
- Oh, for how long?
- Forever.

00:17.769 --> 00:19.526
Max?

00:19.560 --> 00:22.429
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

00:22.463 --> 00:23.730
<i>♪ </i>

00:23.765 --> 00:25.332
<i>[James Vincent McMorrow's</i>

00:25.366 --> 00:27.200
<i>["EARLY IN THE MORNING,
I'LL COME CALLING"]</i>

00:27.235 --> 00:30.904
<i>♪ Early in the morning,
I'll come calling ♪</i>

00:30.939 --> 00:34.541
<i>♪ I'll come calling after you ♪</i>

00:35.610 --> 00:40.013
<i>♪ Darling, if you answer,
oh, we'll wander ♪</i>

00:40.048 --> 00:44.084
<i>♪ Down the garden where it's cool ♪</i>

00:44.118 --> 00:48.956
<i>♪ Later we'd discover, all in covers ♪</i>

00:48.990 --> 00:52.459
<i>♪ Children silent as the stars ♪</i>

00:52.493 --> 00:57.397
<i>♪ Early in the morning,
I'll come calling ♪</i>

00:57.432 --> 01:01.768
<i>♪ I'll come calling after you ♪</i>

01:01.803 --> 01:04.104
- [PHONE VIBRATING]
<i>- ♪ Though you seldom answer ♪</i>

01:04.138 --> 01:09.977
<i>♪ Still I wonder, what will</i>
<i>pass here when you do? ♪</i> _

01:10.011 --> 01:16.183
<i>♪ Crisp and pressed and blue ♪</i>

01:17.352 --> 01:21.221
<i>[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY OVER PA]</i>

01:21.255 --> 01:25.058
Wow, Dora, you really are
as terrifying as Max says.

01:25.093 --> 01:26.760
And I'm going easy 'cause you're

01:26.794 --> 01:28.462
new to the role of medical director.

01:28.496 --> 01:31.064
Deputy medical director.
I'm only taking on Max's duties

01:31.099 --> 01:32.454
while he's recuperating.

01:32.488 --> 01:34.167
Yeah, well, you're ten minutes late

01:34.202 --> 01:36.236
to your first meeting,
which is a baller move

01:36.270 --> 01:37.504
so soon into your tenure.

01:37.538 --> 01:39.239
I'm on my way.

01:39.273 --> 01:42.669
Could you, um, message this
to Dr. Valentina Castro?

01:42.703 --> 01:43.910
Max's DNA?

01:43.945 --> 01:45.846
Please don't Jurassic Park him.

01:45.880 --> 01:47.481
One Max is more than I can handle.

01:47.515 --> 01:49.316
It's for a new treatment,
one that will get him back

01:49.350 --> 01:51.918
into the hospital ASAP,
so I no longer have to be...

01:51.953 --> 01:54.521
Sharpe, just the medical
director I was looking for.

01:54.555 --> 01:56.301
[CHUCKLES] Deputy medical director.

01:56.335 --> 01:57.475
How can I help?

01:57.500 --> 02:00.208
Oh I, um... I need ecstasy.

02:01.029 --> 02:03.255
Like, the feeling of bliss?

02:03.255 --> 02:05.723
Like MDMA, like drugs.

02:05.758 --> 02:09.294
[CHUCKLES] Is this a joke?

02:09.328 --> 02:10.929
Am I being hazed?

02:10.963 --> 02:12.797
No, we don't... we don't
do that anymore, right?

02:12.832 --> 02:14.799
Uh, no, I have a patient
who is exhibiting

02:14.834 --> 02:16.901
the most aggressive PTSD
I think I've ever seen.

02:16.936 --> 02:18.570
Kapoor and I've tried everything.

02:18.604 --> 02:21.005
Nothing makes a dent, so I would like you

02:21.040 --> 02:23.174
to sign my new treatment strategy.

02:23.209 --> 02:24.576
Max thoroughly approved.

02:24.610 --> 02:26.644
Oh-ho. Was he high at the time?

02:26.679 --> 02:27.946
No, but he actually made that same joke

02:27.980 --> 02:30.081
when he approved it, so it's cool.

02:30.115 --> 02:31.950
It's a good joke, I think.
Great minds, right?

02:31.984 --> 02:34.118
Listen, I assure you MDMA,
under the proper supervision,

02:34.153 --> 02:35.820
allows a patient
to confront their memories

02:35.855 --> 02:37.355
in a trigger-free environment...
it's amazing.

02:37.389 --> 02:39.858
Yeah, see you later.
It teaches them to remember

02:39.892 --> 02:42.260
a traumatic event instead of reliving it.

02:42.294 --> 02:44.462
All right, either you sign
so I can get the pure stuff

02:44.496 --> 02:46.664
from upstairs, or I'm gonna
have to go score from a guy

02:46.699 --> 02:50.335
named Rocket who lives
in his grandmother's basement.

02:50.369 --> 02:52.303
Yeah, just... Okay, fine.

02:52.338 --> 02:54.172
Aces.

02:54.206 --> 02:55.673
[SIGHS]

02:55.708 --> 02:59.777
Wow, signing off on illicit
drugs on your first day.

02:59.812 --> 03:00.812
Hmm.

03:00.846 --> 03:02.847
<i>[PERCUSSIVE MUSIC]</i>

03:02.882 --> 03:04.616
- Yeah.
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]

03:04.650 --> 03:06.384
[LAUGHTER]

03:06.418 --> 03:08.987
Oh, my gosh, that's true, though.

03:09.021 --> 03:10.555
How long have you all had this tradition?

03:10.589 --> 03:12.957
Oh, how many Sunday's is in forever?

03:12.992 --> 03:15.694
- Mom!
- Hey, uh, Jayden...

03:15.735 --> 03:18.796
No matter how old we got,
Mama has always made sure

03:18.831 --> 03:21.232
we're here every Sunday
eating her food, right?

03:21.267 --> 03:23.534
It's been family tradition
since before I was born.

03:23.569 --> 03:27.005
Sunday means church, family,
and a meal with two meats.

03:27.039 --> 03:28.806
- No exceptions.
- That's right.

03:28.841 --> 03:30.241
- Right?
- Yep, yep.

03:30.276 --> 03:31.643
[LAUGHS]

03:31.677 --> 03:34.178
My family never did the church thing,

03:34.213 --> 03:35.713
but we're very spiritual.

03:35.748 --> 03:37.805
- Hmm.
- Uh, which spirit?

03:40.085 --> 03:41.719
- [CLEARS THROAT] Uh, Brandi...
- Hmm?

03:41.754 --> 03:44.222
Don't make me bust out
the drill team photos.

03:44.256 --> 03:46.724
Oh, uh, okay, Foofy.

03:46.759 --> 03:49.093
ALL: Ooh! [LAUGHTER]

03:49.128 --> 03:50.495
All right, forget the drill team photos.

03:50.529 --> 03:52.163
I'm busting out prom.

03:52.197 --> 03:56.000
- Everybody look right here.
- Two words... sportin' waves.

03:56.035 --> 03:57.702
I'm gonna put you both in the corner

03:57.736 --> 04:00.071
- if you can't find your manners.
- [LAUGHTER]

04:00.105 --> 04:03.841
So, Evie, you're a lawyer
at Floyd's hospital?

04:03.876 --> 04:05.510
Well, I-I got there first, actually.

04:05.544 --> 04:07.712
- Oh?
- By one week.

04:07.746 --> 04:10.949
Okay. I did my undergrad at Yale,

04:10.983 --> 04:14.118
and I went to, uh...
I went to law school at NYU.

04:14.153 --> 04:15.853
So I did have a leg up on the city.

04:15.888 --> 04:18.523
Oh, I had the HBCU experience.

04:18.557 --> 04:20.379
Do they have Greeks at Yale?

04:20.413 --> 04:21.526
I pledged AKA.

04:21.560 --> 04:23.528
Oh, hey Soror.

04:23.562 --> 04:25.096
- No way!
- Oh, yes.

04:25.130 --> 04:26.137
Oh, my goodness.

04:26.172 --> 04:29.067
[LAUGHS] Oh, I knew I liked her.

04:29.101 --> 04:30.535
[LAUGHTER]

04:30.569 --> 04:34.138
Okay, I hear you. I hear you.

04:34.173 --> 04:36.741
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

04:40.593 --> 04:42.245
There you go.

04:44.183 --> 04:45.650
Sorry.

04:45.684 --> 04:47.151
[DOOR CLOSES]

04:47.186 --> 04:49.420
Keep in mind,
Dr. Kapoor and I will be here

04:49.455 --> 04:51.212
with you the entire time.

04:56.217 --> 04:59.137
Jacob, you don't have to do
this, obviously, but...

04:59.598 --> 05:02.066
before you say no, can I just ask,

05:02.101 --> 05:05.643
when was the last time
a loud noise didn't scare you?

05:06.205 --> 05:09.147
Or when was the last time you
felt safe in a crowded room?

05:09.708 --> 05:11.691
Or slept without nightmares?

05:12.678 --> 05:14.746
You cannot keep going through life

05:14.780 --> 05:17.029
feeling like everyone is a threat.

05:17.616 --> 05:19.017
But they are.

05:19.051 --> 05:22.086
Just turn on the news...
hate crimes, wars,

05:22.121 --> 05:24.922
they put kids in cages, and no one cares.

05:24.957 --> 05:27.592
It's not PTSD. People are a threat.

05:27.626 --> 05:29.542
People are evil.

05:30.329 --> 05:33.463
Do you know what the
cruelest symptom of PTSD is?

05:35.006 --> 05:36.424
It's a thief.

05:37.300 --> 05:40.136
It robs us of the ability
to see the light.

05:41.173 --> 05:43.141
But that doesn't mean it's not there.

05:43.175 --> 05:48.146
Do you remember how it felt
when the world had light?

05:51.689 --> 05:55.620
This process is how you get
that light back, Jacob.

05:55.654 --> 05:58.456
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

05:58.490 --> 06:02.560
<i>♪ </i>

06:02.594 --> 06:04.629
[SIGHS]

06:04.663 --> 06:11.869
<i>♪ </i>

06:13.000 --> 06:19.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

06:20.345 --> 06:24.315
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

06:24.349 --> 06:26.017
Max?

06:28.195 --> 06:29.754
- Max.
- [LOCK CLICKS]

06:29.788 --> 06:32.757
<i>[TENSE MUSIC]</i>

06:32.791 --> 06:35.093
<i>♪ </i>

06:35.127 --> 06:36.566
No, it's not me. It's Georgia.

06:36.600 --> 06:37.929
What happened?

06:37.963 --> 06:39.730
Uh, the placenta previa ruptured.

06:39.765 --> 06:41.833
- I was about to call 911.
- Do it now.

06:41.867 --> 06:44.202
- [DOOR CLOSES]
- [BREATHING SHAKILY]

06:44.236 --> 06:46.270
The blood, it happened so fast.

06:46.305 --> 06:47.572
Okay, we need to get you off the floor.

06:47.606 --> 06:49.073
- Max?
<i>- [LINE TRILLING]</i>

06:49.108 --> 06:51.008
No, I-I was too weak.
I couldn't lift her.

06:51.043 --> 06:52.443
Okay, well, now you got me.

06:52.478 --> 06:53.845
Come on. Ready? One, two, three.

06:53.879 --> 06:55.847
<i>911, what's your emergency?</i>

06:55.881 --> 06:57.115
Max, 911.

06:57.149 --> 06:58.516
<i>911, what's your emergency?</i>

06:58.550 --> 07:00.118
- Any fever? Chills?
- Um, no.

07:00.152 --> 07:01.240
- Any contractions?
- No.

07:01.275 --> 07:03.354
I need an ambulance to, uh,
42 East 17th Street.

07:03.388 --> 07:05.690
I need paramedics, not EMTs,
and I need you to get here now.

07:05.724 --> 07:06.858
Heart rate up to 180 and thready.

07:06.892 --> 07:08.359
No, no, just get here.

07:08.393 --> 07:10.394
- Is that bad?
- No, just try to relax, okay?

07:10.429 --> 07:13.264
- [BREATHING SHAKILY]
- Max, Max, can I, uh...

07:13.298 --> 07:14.966
Uh, they're 12 minutes out.

07:15.000 --> 07:16.734
That's too far away...
Georgia will bleed out

07:16.768 --> 07:18.736
- before they arrive.
- No, there's time.

07:18.770 --> 07:22.540
Max, she's out of time.
We need to ligate the artery.

07:22.574 --> 07:25.710
<i>♪ </i>

07:25.744 --> 07:27.245
Here?

07:27.279 --> 07:29.213
And now.

07:29.248 --> 07:30.615
<i>♪ </i>

07:30.649 --> 07:32.550
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

07:32.584 --> 07:34.552
[SCOFFS]

07:34.586 --> 07:41.792
<i>♪ </i>

08:01.947 --> 08:04.415
Hey, look at me. I'm right here.

08:04.449 --> 08:05.983
I'm with you, okay?

08:06.018 --> 08:08.159
I'm right here with you.

08:09.288 --> 08:12.924
The fentanyl should already be working.

08:12.958 --> 08:17.351
Okay, you're gonna feel
a slight heaviness,

08:17.396 --> 08:19.497
and then you're gonna drift off to sleep.

08:19.531 --> 08:20.637
Hmm.

08:20.671 --> 08:23.167
And then... and then
we'll be able to operate

08:23.202 --> 08:25.301
without you feeling a thing.

08:28.307 --> 08:32.376
All these drugs, they...
they might hurt her.

08:32.410 --> 08:33.678
Will they hurt her?

08:34.309 --> 08:36.047
It's not gonna hurt the baby.

08:36.081 --> 08:37.948
It's not... it's not gonna hurt her?

08:37.982 --> 08:40.952
No, I promise, no.

08:40.986 --> 08:43.054
The opiate will slow
Luna's heart rate a little,

08:43.087 --> 08:46.113
but we'll be monitoring her
every step of the way.

08:46.758 --> 08:48.626
[SIGHS]

08:48.660 --> 08:50.201
Okay.

08:50.696 --> 08:52.828
Hey, it's gonna work.

08:53.365 --> 08:55.520
It's gonna work. It's gonna work.

08:55.554 --> 08:58.970
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

08:59.004 --> 09:02.740
<i>♪ </i>

09:02.774 --> 09:07.093
I don't want Luna to have to
take ballet because of me, Max.

09:08.552 --> 09:10.314
No, no, she won't.

09:10.349 --> 09:12.583
<i>♪ </i>

09:12.618 --> 09:15.319
I want her to experience everything...

09:15.354 --> 09:17.561
[SNIFFLES] Everything...

09:18.624 --> 09:20.825
rock climbing...

09:20.859 --> 09:22.775
and clarinet...

09:23.528 --> 09:24.829
and painting.

09:24.863 --> 09:26.530
She will.

09:26.565 --> 09:29.115
No, you have to encourage her, Max.

09:30.282 --> 09:32.326
You have to help her.

09:32.871 --> 09:35.706
You have to help her
find her own voice...

09:35.741 --> 09:37.508
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

09:37.542 --> 09:38.876
Her own path.

09:38.910 --> 09:41.335
We can encourage her together...

09:42.047 --> 09:43.848
you and me.

09:43.882 --> 09:46.550
<i>♪ </i>

09:46.585 --> 09:47.852
But if I don't...

09:47.886 --> 09:50.755
- Stop, stop. No.
- If I don't, Max...

09:51.220 --> 09:52.523
No.

09:54.059 --> 09:57.127
I need you to promise me something.

09:57.161 --> 09:59.864
<i>♪ </i>

09:59.898 --> 10:02.566
Promise me that you'll save her...

10:02.601 --> 10:04.568
save her first.

10:04.603 --> 10:07.038
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

10:07.072 --> 10:08.873
Promise, I need you to promise me.

10:09.280 --> 10:11.409
Promise you'll save our baby girl.

10:11.443 --> 10:13.444
<i>♪ </i>

10:13.478 --> 10:16.547
Promise me, no matter what.

10:16.581 --> 10:19.717
[SIGHS]

10:19.751 --> 10:21.619
I...

10:22.921 --> 10:24.555
Promise me.

10:24.589 --> 10:31.295
<i>♪ </i>

10:32.664 --> 10:34.398
Max...

10:34.433 --> 10:36.400
it's time.

10:36.435 --> 10:43.474
<i>♪ </i>

10:49.221 --> 10:51.488
Let me go! Will you guys
just listen to me?

10:51.522 --> 10:52.822
<i>Nice save, Victoria.</i>
I have done nothing wrong.

10:52.857 --> 10:54.758
Yeah, what all innocent people scream.

10:54.792 --> 10:56.826
- This lunatic...
- My name is Wilson Hatch.

10:56.861 --> 10:58.461
This lunatic, Wilson Hatch,

10:58.496 --> 11:00.497
swallowed the biggest balloon
of cocaine I've ever seen.

11:00.531 --> 11:01.931
- No, no.
- We need an X-ray

11:01.966 --> 11:04.068
of his abdomen so we can
get him on intent to sell.

11:04.102 --> 11:05.662
This is... Okay, this might
fly with people

11:05.696 --> 11:07.358
who don't know any better,
but I am a partner

11:07.399 --> 11:09.314
at Wyman, Frost, and Handle.

11:09.348 --> 11:10.829
I know my rights.
You guys have nothing on me.

11:10.854 --> 11:12.522
I'm out of here. I'm done. I'm leaving.

11:12.556 --> 11:13.990
Yeah, you're leaving...
you're leaving this floor

11:14.024 --> 11:15.458
and heading up to radiology.

11:15.492 --> 11:17.306
- Let's go, buddy.
- I don't consent to that.

11:18.262 --> 11:21.064
Ow, Mom. How you gonna do me like that?

11:21.098 --> 11:24.133
I love you, but you take food
with your bare hands,

11:24.168 --> 11:25.969
I'll put you over my knee.

11:26.003 --> 11:27.236
I can't help it.

11:27.271 --> 11:28.399
It's so good,
and I can't live without it,

11:28.433 --> 11:29.465
just like I can't live without you.

11:29.499 --> 11:31.507
- Oh.
- [CHUCKLES]

11:31.542 --> 11:34.377
So she's amazing, right?

11:34.945 --> 11:36.846
She's an exceptional young lady.

11:36.880 --> 11:39.749
Good, I was hoping
you'd say that because...

11:39.783 --> 11:41.084
it's time...

11:41.118 --> 11:42.819
for me to use the family ring.

11:42.853 --> 11:44.554
Oh, honey.

11:44.588 --> 11:45.687
What?

11:45.721 --> 11:48.925
Evie seems like the perfect woman,

11:48.959 --> 11:51.494
just not the perfect woman for you.

11:51.528 --> 11:55.531
[INDISTINCT CHATTER, LAUGHTER]

11:55.566 --> 11:57.500
- [MONITOR WHIRRING]
- Don't want to pull too hard.

11:57.534 --> 12:00.269
A half hedge
will fully occlude the artery.

12:00.304 --> 12:02.438
[WHIRRING CONTINUES]

12:02.473 --> 12:05.208
- [SIGHS]
- That should do it.

12:05.242 --> 12:07.410
Bleeding should be under control.

12:07.444 --> 12:11.114
[MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY]

12:11.148 --> 12:12.415
Huh?

12:12.449 --> 12:14.572
Georgia's having a contraction.

12:15.285 --> 12:17.120
It... it... it's squeezing the cord.

12:17.154 --> 12:18.721
Heart rate down to 40.

12:18.756 --> 12:20.690
If it goes any lower, it... it... uh...

12:20.724 --> 12:23.292
Uh, we... we need to stop
the contraction.

12:23.327 --> 12:25.194
I can't. It can only pass...

12:25.229 --> 12:27.630
[MONITOR BEEPS STEADILY,
WHIRRING CONTINUES]

12:27.665 --> 12:29.766
By itself.

12:30.667 --> 12:32.368
Max...

12:33.415 --> 12:35.705
The baby won't survive another one.

12:35.739 --> 12:38.241
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

12:38.275 --> 12:40.109
So we have to get her out.

12:40.144 --> 12:41.477
There'll be too much blood loss,

12:41.512 --> 12:43.146
Georgia's lost enough as it is.

12:43.180 --> 12:44.647
No, you did one surgery,
you can do another.

12:44.682 --> 12:47.150
Except this time, Georgia will die.

12:47.184 --> 12:49.152
<i>♪ </i>

12:49.186 --> 12:50.653
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

12:50.688 --> 12:53.622
[CELL PHONE RINGS]
- Yes, Max, the hospital

12:53.657 --> 12:55.491
is still here, so you can go back to bed.

12:55.526 --> 12:57.660
I need you to listen to me.

12:57.695 --> 12:59.662
911 dispatched
an ambulance to my apartment,

12:59.697 --> 13:01.230
<i>but they don't have
everything that we need.</i>

13:01.265 --> 13:02.999
An ambulance? Why?

13:03.033 --> 13:05.103
<i>I need you to call dispatch
and have them go back</i>

13:05.137 --> 13:07.210
<i>to the station, and... and,
uh, they need to pick up</i>

13:07.244 --> 13:09.203
<i>trauma dressing and
surgical gloves and oxygen,</i>

13:09.228 --> 13:10.695
<i>and then I need a second ambulance</i>

13:10.729 --> 13:12.430
<i>from New Amsterdam that's fully stocked</i>

13:12.464 --> 13:15.137
<i>with B-positive blood and mifepristone.</i>

13:15.171 --> 13:18.002
I'm doing it now. Max, what's happening?

13:18.037 --> 13:20.596
I'm trying to save my family.

13:23.642 --> 13:25.443
We just finished finals.

13:25.477 --> 13:29.013
Third year, never have
to take a test again, so...

13:29.048 --> 13:30.615
we went out to celebrate.

13:30.649 --> 13:32.107
Who's we?

13:32.617 --> 13:34.351
I can't remember exactly.

13:34.376 --> 13:36.177
Try.

13:36.202 --> 13:39.170
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

13:39.195 --> 13:43.665
<i>♪ </i>

13:43.829 --> 13:46.798
<i>[DISTANT CLUB MUSIC]</i>

13:46.832 --> 13:48.700
It's me...

13:48.734 --> 13:50.980
Bobby, and Emma.

13:51.014 --> 13:55.139
[MUSIC STOPS]

13:55.174 --> 13:56.974
We're outside the door.

13:57.009 --> 13:59.811
<i>[MUSIC RESUMES]</i>

13:59.845 --> 14:01.145
<i>♪ </i>

14:01.180 --> 14:02.714
What happened next?

14:02.748 --> 14:05.917
<i>[MUSIC INTENSIFIES]</i>

14:05.951 --> 14:11.656
<i>♪ </i>

14:11.690 --> 14:13.190
You got a problem?

14:13.552 --> 14:14.986
Perhaps we should wait.

14:15.011 --> 14:16.452
No, no, no, no, he...

14:16.477 --> 14:18.337
he's not talking to me.

14:18.362 --> 14:20.997
<i>♪ </i>

14:21.200 --> 14:22.400
Hey!

14:22.434 --> 14:23.634
He said...

14:23.669 --> 14:25.494
You got a problem?

14:25.971 --> 14:28.940
Jacob, leave it alone.

14:28.974 --> 14:30.842
<i>This guy just bumps into me.</i>

14:30.876 --> 14:32.076
He's big.

14:32.111 --> 14:36.481
<i>♪ </i>

14:36.515 --> 14:38.015
- [HIGH-PITCHED RINGING]
- It's all right, Jacob.

14:38.050 --> 14:39.983
We're right here with you. It's okay.

14:40.376 --> 14:41.715
It's okay It's okay, Jacob.

14:41.750 --> 14:44.522
Hey, we're right here with you, Jacob.

14:44.556 --> 14:47.458
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

14:47.493 --> 14:51.529
I... I didn't know it was
a pipe bomb when it happened.

14:51.563 --> 14:54.532
<i>[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]</i>

14:54.566 --> 14:57.969
<i>♪ </i>

14:58.003 --> 15:01.305
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

15:01.340 --> 15:04.442
I see Emma. She's...

15:04.476 --> 15:06.160
Emma?

15:07.746 --> 15:09.480
[SCREAMS] Help!

15:09.515 --> 15:12.116
This piece of stone is crushing her.

15:12.151 --> 15:14.051
<i>She... she can't breathe.</i>

15:14.086 --> 15:16.253
I have to get her out, but...

15:17.139 --> 15:18.425
it's too heavy.

15:18.459 --> 15:21.025
Please, somebody help me!

15:21.059 --> 15:23.060
If just one person helps me,
I can get it off.

15:23.095 --> 15:25.129
Just one person, but no one helps.

15:25.164 --> 15:27.965
Not Bobby, not... not anyone.

15:29.535 --> 15:32.170
Ah!

15:32.204 --> 15:36.507
Now they're trampling me,
and I can't move,

15:36.542 --> 15:39.510
<i>And she's dying. No one will help.</i>

15:39.545 --> 15:41.879
They're all running right over us.

15:41.914 --> 15:44.182
- [PEOPLE SCREAMING]
- Watch it!

15:44.216 --> 15:47.518
[SOBBING] Why would he do that?

15:47.553 --> 15:50.298
- [SOBS]
- It's okay... it's okay, Jacob.

15:50.332 --> 15:52.690
No, why would he do that?

15:52.724 --> 15:53.914
It's okay. It's okay. Just breathe.

15:53.948 --> 15:55.494
Help me.

15:55.528 --> 15:57.241
Help me, Dr. Frome. Help me.

15:57.275 --> 15:59.764
[GASPING]

15:59.798 --> 16:03.034
Please, Dr. Frome, help me.

16:03.068 --> 16:04.735
[BREATHING FRANTICALLY]

16:04.770 --> 16:06.571
I'm sorry, Jacob. I need... I need to...

16:06.605 --> 16:08.105
I need something

16:08.140 --> 16:09.745
Dr. Frome, what's happening?

16:09.779 --> 16:11.679
Dr. Frome, what's happening?

16:11.713 --> 16:14.111
<i>♪ </i>

16:14.146 --> 16:15.809
You're in New Amsterdam Hospital.

16:15.844 --> 16:17.515
- You're in Manhattan.
- Where is she?

16:17.549 --> 16:19.283
- What's happening?
- You're... you're safe.

16:19.318 --> 16:21.452
- Dr. Frome, where is he?
- [DOOR CLOSES]

16:21.487 --> 16:23.287
Take the FDR, anything else
will take too long.

16:23.322 --> 16:24.698
And remember, when you get
there, cut up early.

16:24.733 --> 16:25.758
It's a one-way.

16:25.793 --> 16:27.792
Wait! Wait, I'm coming.

16:27.826 --> 16:30.441
Dr. Sharpe, you cannot leave.
You are the medical director.

16:30.441 --> 16:33.276
And I learned from the best.

16:33.311 --> 16:36.212
[SIREN WAILING]

16:37.930 --> 16:41.131
[MONITOR WHIRRING]

16:44.569 --> 16:49.935
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

16:49.969 --> 16:53.768
Max, uh, we need to talk
about what happens if...

16:53.793 --> 16:55.269
They'll get here.

16:56.796 --> 16:58.864
If Georgia has another contraction,

16:59.203 --> 17:01.238
there's not gonna be time to talk.

17:01.272 --> 17:03.006
I'm gonna have to deliver the baby,

17:03.031 --> 17:04.665
or we're risking both their lives.

17:04.709 --> 17:06.655
But if you open her up...

17:07.878 --> 17:09.782
before the blood gets here,

17:10.714 --> 17:12.368
she might not make it.

17:13.550 --> 17:18.188
Which is why we need to decide who...

17:18.750 --> 17:20.357
No, they'll get here.

17:20.391 --> 17:22.025
They have to.

17:22.060 --> 17:24.194
<i>♪ </i>

17:24.882 --> 17:27.030
I've been so selfish...

17:27.065 --> 17:29.132
<i>♪ </i>

17:29.167 --> 17:33.370
Thinking that I was the one...
who wouldn't survive.

17:33.404 --> 17:35.539
I never even stopped to think, what if...

17:35.573 --> 17:38.542
<i>♪ </i>

17:38.576 --> 17:40.647
Georgia...

17:42.914 --> 17:45.115
[CRIES] And Luna.

17:45.149 --> 17:48.071
You know what?
It's okay. We don't have to...

17:49.187 --> 17:52.723
Um, If you hadn't shown up
when you did...

17:52.757 --> 17:55.225
I don't know what I would've done.

17:55.259 --> 17:57.394
[WHIRRING CONTINUES]

17:57.428 --> 18:03.233
<i>♪ </i>

18:03.267 --> 18:05.214
Thank God you're here.

18:06.104 --> 18:08.300
By the way... [CHUCKLES]

18:10.708 --> 18:12.576
Why are you here?

18:12.610 --> 18:15.160
<i>♪ </i>

18:15.194 --> 18:17.147
We can talk about that later.

18:17.181 --> 18:22.919
<i>♪ </i>

18:22.954 --> 18:26.857
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

18:27.792 --> 18:30.594
- You can't keep ignoring me.
- I'm not ignoring you.

18:30.628 --> 18:32.062
We've got guests,

18:32.096 --> 18:34.097
and these dishes are not gonna
walk themselves in.

18:34.132 --> 18:35.766
You're always reminding me
how you're saving

18:35.800 --> 18:37.934
the family ring for me, and now
I finally want to use it.

18:37.969 --> 18:41.505
All your adult life you keep
telling me about your plan,

18:41.539 --> 18:45.175
that you want your new family
to look like this one.

18:45.209 --> 18:46.576
Yeah, I still do.

18:46.611 --> 18:48.111
And how's that gonna happen with Evie?

18:48.146 --> 18:50.113
She doesn't even go to church.

18:50.148 --> 18:52.249
Ma, that doesn't mean that I can't.

18:52.283 --> 18:54.885
I even noticed that Evie doesn't cook.

18:54.919 --> 18:56.253
Doesn't cook 'cause she can't.

18:56.287 --> 18:57.954
She... she works 12 hours a day.

18:57.989 --> 19:00.023
So is she giving that up...

19:00.058 --> 19:03.460
when you have your kids?

19:03.494 --> 19:04.428
Are you?

19:04.462 --> 19:06.463
[SIGHS] I don't know.

19:06.497 --> 19:07.731
Exactly.

19:07.765 --> 19:10.200
Come back for the ring when you do know.

19:10.234 --> 19:14.071
[INDISTINCT CHATTER, DISHES CLATTER]

19:15.840 --> 19:18.475
[SIGHS] Don't say it.

19:18.509 --> 19:20.310
She just wants you to be happy.

19:20.344 --> 19:23.647
No, she wants me
to marry somebody like her.

19:23.681 --> 19:26.483
'Cause that's how you
get a family like this.

19:26.517 --> 19:30.087
No judgment... that's just the reality.

19:31.258 --> 19:33.790
A life with Evie
isn't gonna look like this.

19:33.825 --> 19:36.159
It's not gonna look
like what you planned,

19:36.194 --> 19:38.662
and Mama's smart enough to see that.

19:38.696 --> 19:40.001
Why can't you?

19:40.036 --> 19:44.000
<i>[LIGHT MUSIC]</i>

19:44.035 --> 19:46.002
<i>♪ </i>

19:46.037 --> 19:48.271
[INDISTINCT CHATTER, LAUGHTER]

19:48.306 --> 19:54.111
<i>♪ </i>

19:54.145 --> 19:56.199
He's calmer now.

19:57.047 --> 19:58.614
Good.

19:59.897 --> 20:01.631
Thank you.

20:11.462 --> 20:13.530
When Jacob started
to break down in there,

20:13.564 --> 20:15.093
my instinct was...

20:16.720 --> 20:18.472
It was to hold him.

20:19.237 --> 20:21.872
That seemed like
the appropriate response.

20:21.906 --> 20:23.560
But I can't...

20:25.103 --> 20:26.543
not after what happened with Avi.

20:26.577 --> 20:28.145
I can't do that.

20:30.734 --> 20:32.486
So I just froze.

20:34.029 --> 20:36.019
This is different than Avi.

20:36.053 --> 20:37.954
No, it's not.

20:37.989 --> 20:41.151
<i>[SOMBER MUSIC]</i>

20:41.186 --> 20:42.954
I feel like...

20:44.262 --> 20:46.708
the physical contact...

20:48.099 --> 20:49.733
is all I have.

20:49.767 --> 20:51.568
<i>♪ </i>

20:51.602 --> 20:55.759
It's... it's my crutch, you know?

20:56.593 --> 20:58.742
The only thing I have
in my bag of tricks.

20:58.776 --> 21:00.877
<i>♪ </i>

21:00.912 --> 21:04.518
Iggy, sometimes people need
the physical contact...

21:05.435 --> 21:07.187
to feel cared for.

21:08.230 --> 21:12.255
But it's not the only trick you have.

21:12.290 --> 21:16.092
It just heightens your other gifts.

21:16.127 --> 21:18.094
You can't doubt that.

21:18.129 --> 21:20.697
<i>♪ </i>

21:20.731 --> 21:22.619
But I do...

21:24.302 --> 21:26.269
all the time now.

21:26.304 --> 21:28.605
<i>♪ </i>

21:28.639 --> 21:30.507
How can I get inside someone else's head

21:30.541 --> 21:32.609
if I can't get out of my own?

21:32.643 --> 21:35.912
<i>♪ </i>

21:35.947 --> 21:38.927
You're always the one who counsels me...

21:39.928 --> 21:41.952
and you have taught me very well.

21:41.986 --> 21:44.221
<i>♪ </i>

21:44.255 --> 21:46.768
So what I'll say to you is this...

21:48.061 --> 21:50.188
that boy needs help...

21:51.495 --> 21:53.728
and you are the only one
who can help him.

21:54.799 --> 22:01.872
<i>♪ </i>

22:04.175 --> 22:07.310
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

22:07.345 --> 22:10.413
[ALARM SOUNDING, MONITOR WHIRRING]

22:10.448 --> 22:12.749
Heart rate's fluctuating.

22:12.783 --> 22:14.818
The contractions have
started... I have to cut.

22:14.852 --> 22:16.786
No, wait, wait, wait.
They're close, okay?

22:16.821 --> 22:18.221
- Max...
- No, they're gonna be close.

22:18.256 --> 22:20.090
Just... just wait.

22:20.124 --> 22:23.326
[CELL PHONE BEEPING]

22:23.361 --> 22:25.161
Hey, hey, tell me you guys
will make it here

22:25.196 --> 22:26.663
in the next three minutes.

22:26.697 --> 22:28.431
We're close, Dr. Goodwin.
The other bus is right...

22:28.466 --> 22:30.166
- Give it to me.
- Sure.

22:30.201 --> 22:32.168
Max, it's Helen. Talk to me.

22:32.203 --> 22:34.738
Luna's heart rate is fading
with each contraction.

22:34.772 --> 22:36.406
We could lose her on the next one.

22:36.440 --> 22:37.841
<i>But if Bloom operates now...
Bloom's there?</i>

22:37.875 --> 22:39.676
Yeah, she saved Georgia's life.

22:39.710 --> 22:43.146
But if she operates and
you are not close enough,

22:43.180 --> 22:45.248
then she could bleed out.

22:45.283 --> 22:47.017
<i>Oh, God...</i>

22:47.051 --> 22:48.184
What? What?

22:48.219 --> 22:50.020
Max, we are not close enough.

22:50.054 --> 22:52.022
<i>♪ </i>

22:52.056 --> 22:53.356
Yeah, no, but you...

22:53.391 --> 22:55.295
We're not gonna make it.

22:56.060 --> 22:57.593
Max?

22:57.628 --> 23:01.557
<i>♪ </i>

23:01.591 --> 23:03.199
<i>Are you still there?</i>

23:03.234 --> 23:05.835
<i>[SIRENS WAILING OVER PHONE]</i>

23:05.870 --> 23:09.539
<i>♪ </i>

23:09.573 --> 23:11.353
Yeah.

23:13.605 --> 23:15.045
After everything you have done,

23:15.079 --> 23:18.481
I would jump out of here, and
I would run the blood to you

23:18.516 --> 23:20.150
<i>if I thought that it would help,</i>

23:20.184 --> 23:22.886
<i>but we are not close enough.</i>

23:23.615 --> 23:25.322
<i>I'm, uh...</i>

23:25.909 --> 23:28.224
I'm so sorry.

23:29.079 --> 23:30.580
[SCOFFS]

23:31.262 --> 23:33.208
- [CELL PHONE BEEPS]
- I have to...

23:34.565 --> 23:38.234
I have to choose between
my wife and my... and my...

23:38.269 --> 23:41.071
No, no. Okay, look.

23:41.105 --> 23:43.218
Hey, listen to me.

23:44.427 --> 23:48.578
This is a decision that...
that you cannot make...

23:48.612 --> 23:50.517
'cause whatever you decide,

23:51.601 --> 23:54.084
you're gonna be haunted by it
for the rest of your life.

23:54.688 --> 23:56.586
I've seen it, Max.

23:57.023 --> 24:00.068
The guilt, the shame...

24:00.791 --> 24:02.258
The loss.

24:03.321 --> 24:04.995
It'll destroy you, Max.

24:05.407 --> 24:07.263
But I have... I have to.

24:07.298 --> 24:10.767
<i>♪ </i>

24:10.801 --> 24:12.268
I'll do it.

24:12.303 --> 24:15.109
<i>♪ </i>

24:15.143 --> 24:17.374
I'll decide.

24:17.408 --> 24:19.509
I'll take on the responsibility.

24:19.543 --> 24:22.445
[BREATHING SHARPLY]

24:22.480 --> 24:25.260
Please, Max, please...

24:26.150 --> 24:28.451
let me do this for you.

24:28.486 --> 24:35.725
<i>♪ </i>

24:36.594 --> 24:39.295
[SOBS SOFTLY] Okay.

24:39.330 --> 24:41.631
<i>♪ </i>

24:42.527 --> 24:45.155
Try to cast your mind back to that night.

24:46.197 --> 24:49.706
What was the last exam you
and your friends had taken?

24:50.452 --> 24:52.142
I don't...

24:52.176 --> 24:53.910
I don't remember.

24:53.944 --> 24:56.041
- [DOOR BANGS OPEN]
- [CLEARS THROAT]

25:01.752 --> 25:03.387
[CLEARS THROAT]

25:03.412 --> 25:04.745
Jacob...

25:06.624 --> 25:08.591
Jacob, when you were talking
about being trampled

25:08.626 --> 25:10.388
by people earlier,

25:11.222 --> 25:13.433
you said, "Why would he do that?"

25:14.392 --> 25:16.066
Okay.

25:16.603 --> 25:19.169
Why would you refer to a
whole crowd of people

25:19.439 --> 25:21.104
as "he"?

25:22.606 --> 25:26.476
Person after person
running by you, over you,

25:26.510 --> 25:29.412
and you said, "Why would he do that?"

25:29.447 --> 25:31.081
That's not what I meant.

25:33.217 --> 25:34.851
I think it was.

25:35.413 --> 25:38.421
Jacob, what really happened that night?

25:41.211 --> 25:43.526
Don't you think it's time to find out?

25:43.561 --> 25:47.197
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

25:47.231 --> 25:48.969
Georgia's pulse?

25:50.234 --> 25:51.868
Steady.

25:51.902 --> 25:53.503
<i>♪ </i>

25:53.537 --> 25:55.038
I can't get it.

25:55.072 --> 25:57.540
<i>♪ </i>

25:58.019 --> 25:59.509
The cord is crimped.

25:59.543 --> 26:01.211
Can you free it?

26:01.245 --> 26:02.812
I'm trying.

26:02.847 --> 26:04.647
[GROANS]

26:04.682 --> 26:06.382
- Come on, baby, come on.
- Easy, easy.

26:06.417 --> 26:08.051
Easy, easy.

26:08.085 --> 26:10.386
- All right, you got it.
- Okay.

26:10.421 --> 26:12.555
Okay, I got it.

26:12.590 --> 26:15.125
- Okay.
- Easy.

26:15.159 --> 26:16.860
<i>♪ </i>

26:16.894 --> 26:20.897
Okay. Oh, there you go, baby.
There you go, baby.

26:20.931 --> 26:23.066
[SIGHS WITH RELIEF]

26:23.100 --> 26:27.303
- There she is.
- [BABY CRIES SOFTLY]

26:27.338 --> 26:29.139
Hi, Luna.

26:29.173 --> 26:31.407
Oh, my Lord.

26:31.442 --> 26:32.642
It's okay.

26:32.676 --> 26:35.979
[BABY CRYING]

26:37.381 --> 26:39.649
Hi, hi.

26:40.618 --> 26:42.652
You're okay. Hi.

26:42.686 --> 26:47.190
- [BABY CRYING]
- Hi.

26:47.224 --> 26:48.591
Hi, Luna.

26:48.626 --> 26:50.693
There you are.

26:50.728 --> 26:52.262
You're a mess.

26:52.296 --> 26:53.763
I'm your dad.

26:53.797 --> 26:55.198
I got ya.

26:55.232 --> 26:56.828
[BABY CRIES]

26:56.853 --> 26:57.901
Ready?

26:57.935 --> 26:59.664
Georgia...

27:01.082 --> 27:03.006
she's here.

27:03.040 --> 27:05.341
<i>♪ </i>

27:05.376 --> 27:06.943
Georgia.

27:06.977 --> 27:08.945
Yeah, I know.

27:08.979 --> 27:11.548
<i>♪ </i>

27:11.582 --> 27:13.803
Georgia, she's here.

27:15.953 --> 27:19.155
Hi, we've been waiting so long for you.

27:20.558 --> 27:23.271
You came into this world in a really...

27:23.994 --> 27:26.529
really crazy way, but now you're here.

27:26.564 --> 27:28.234
Now you're here.

27:28.832 --> 27:31.780
[CHUCKLES] Georgia, she's here.

27:32.303 --> 27:33.770
Georgia.

27:33.804 --> 27:36.973
Max, she needs blood...

27:37.410 --> 27:38.975
right now.

27:39.009 --> 27:43.313
<i>♪ </i>

27:43.347 --> 27:45.415
You have to hang in there.

27:46.211 --> 27:48.084
You need to hang in there...

27:49.520 --> 27:53.656
Because I am not doing this without you.

27:53.691 --> 27:56.326
<i>♪ </i>

27:56.360 --> 27:57.827
This little girl...

27:57.861 --> 28:00.496
this little girl, she needs her mom.

28:00.531 --> 28:03.433
<i>♪ </i>

28:03.467 --> 28:05.168
And so do I.

28:05.202 --> 28:12.275
<i>♪ </i>

28:16.348 --> 28:19.091
<i>[THE ANTLERS' "KETTERING"]</i>

28:19.116 --> 28:22.017
♪ <i>I wish that I had known</i> ♪

28:22.052 --> 28:26.021
<i>♪ In that first minute we met ♪</i>

28:26.056 --> 28:28.757
♪ <i>The unpayable debt</i> ♪

28:28.792 --> 28:32.427
♪ <i>That I owed you</i> ♪

28:32.461 --> 28:36.788
<i>♪ Because you've been abused ♪</i>

28:36.823 --> 28:39.842
<i>♪ By the bone that refused you ♪</i>

28:39.867 --> 28:42.569
♪ <i>And you hired me</i> ♪

28:42.603 --> 28:45.105
♪ <i>To make up for that</i> ♪

28:45.139 --> 28:47.607
[PADDLES WHIRRING, THUMP]

28:47.642 --> 28:49.943
♪ <i>Walking in that room</i> ♪

28:49.977 --> 28:53.279
<i>♪ When you had tubes in your arms ♪</i>

28:53.314 --> 28:56.716
<i>♪ Those singing morphine alarms ♪</i>

28:56.751 --> 28:59.519
♪ <i>Out of tune</i> ♪

28:59.553 --> 29:01.087
[WOMAN SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY]

29:01.122 --> 29:04.391
<i>♪ Had you sleeping and eating ♪</i>

29:04.425 --> 29:07.260
♪ <i>And I didn't believe them</i> ♪

29:07.294 --> 29:12.132
<i>♪ When they called you
a hurricane thundercloud ♪</i>

29:12.166 --> 29:14.267
<i>♪ </i>

29:14.301 --> 29:18.471
[EXHALES SHARPLY] Okay, we got a pulse.

29:18.506 --> 29:25.779
<i>♪ </i>

29:28.015 --> 29:30.083
Is she... is she all right?

29:30.117 --> 29:32.052
She's fine.

29:32.086 --> 29:39.125
<i>♪ </i>

29:42.563 --> 29:45.131
It's not happening. It's just a memory.

29:45.156 --> 29:46.523
Say that.

29:46.548 --> 29:48.333
It's just a memory.

29:48.836 --> 29:50.543
So then look at it.

29:51.372 --> 29:53.046
It's okay to look, Jacob.

29:53.708 --> 29:55.508
Watch it!

29:55.543 --> 29:57.217
I don't want to.

29:57.712 --> 30:01.848
Every single detail is in there.

30:02.292 --> 30:04.284
Just close your eyes and look.

30:04.318 --> 30:07.287
<i>[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]</i>

30:07.321 --> 30:14.594
<i>♪ </i>

30:19.233 --> 30:20.967
Em...

30:29.577 --> 30:30.959
It's okay.

30:32.379 --> 30:33.614
It's okay.

30:33.648 --> 30:35.648
It's okay to look
somewhere else, just this once.

30:35.683 --> 30:37.550
Where's your other friend from the line?

30:37.585 --> 30:39.452
- Bobby?
- Yeah.

30:39.487 --> 30:41.469
I have no idea.

30:42.142 --> 30:43.763
Sure you do.

30:46.361 --> 30:48.561
He's on the dance floor somewhere.

30:48.596 --> 30:50.296
Facing us?

30:50.331 --> 30:57.370
<i>♪ </i>

30:59.380 --> 31:00.847
Facing away.

31:00.872 --> 31:04.108
Okay. Well, now you know
why he didn't help.

31:04.133 --> 31:06.101
He didn't see us.

31:06.126 --> 31:07.593
No.

31:07.618 --> 31:09.352
What about the big guy,
the guy who bumped into you?

31:09.377 --> 31:10.577
Where's he?

31:10.602 --> 31:12.834
He's on the dance floor somewhere.

31:13.625 --> 31:14.959
You sure?

31:14.993 --> 31:16.927
You said he crashed into you later.

31:16.962 --> 31:19.463
So he couldn't be on the dance
floor when the bomb went off.

31:19.498 --> 31:20.967
He must have been...

31:23.136 --> 31:25.036
Why is he over there?

31:25.070 --> 31:26.848
You tell me.

31:27.839 --> 31:30.307
Wait. I-I hear something.

31:30.342 --> 31:31.976
[AIR HISSING]

31:32.010 --> 31:33.277
What is that?

31:33.311 --> 31:34.545
Take a look.

31:34.579 --> 31:38.549
[HISSING CONTINUES]

31:39.694 --> 31:41.085
It's a gas pipe.

31:41.119 --> 31:43.698
Is that what the guy's looking at?

31:46.358 --> 31:53.597
<i>♪ </i>

31:54.833 --> 31:56.667
That can't be right.

31:57.503 --> 31:59.170
If that happened, I'd be dead.

31:59.204 --> 32:01.007
So why aren't you?

32:01.540 --> 32:03.007
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

32:03.041 --> 32:04.855
Watch out!

32:04.889 --> 32:08.579
[EXPLOSION]

32:13.552 --> 32:15.052
He saved me.

32:16.722 --> 32:18.941
I wasn't being trampled.

32:20.297 --> 32:22.320
I couldn't move because...

32:24.229 --> 32:26.197
he saved me.

32:26.231 --> 32:29.100
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

32:30.569 --> 32:33.081
He risked his life for me.

32:34.239 --> 32:36.107
Why would he do that?

32:36.141 --> 32:37.875
[SIGHS]

32:37.909 --> 32:40.711
Because sometimes the world has light.

32:40.746 --> 32:43.814
<i>[SOFT MUSIC]</i>

32:43.849 --> 32:50.821
<i>♪ </i>

32:50.856 --> 32:54.125
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

33:00.599 --> 33:02.833
[CLEARS THROAT]

33:05.370 --> 33:06.906
Hey.

33:09.608 --> 33:10.841
Hey.

33:10.876 --> 33:12.843
I have to say, you're the last person

33:12.878 --> 33:14.580
I expected to find here.

33:15.947 --> 33:17.792
Yeah, well, me too.

33:18.216 --> 33:21.003
I actually came to tell Max...

33:21.787 --> 33:23.854
that I'm not coming back.

33:25.263 --> 33:26.830
Hell of a last day.

33:27.427 --> 33:28.592
Yeah.

33:28.627 --> 33:31.262
Max would've lost his family

33:31.296 --> 33:33.349
if it wasn't for you.

33:34.633 --> 33:36.477
[SIGHS]

33:37.602 --> 33:40.204
I am so sorry, Lauren.

33:41.143 --> 33:43.107
I'm so very sorry.

33:43.141 --> 33:46.076
I betrayed your trust.
I ruined our friendship.

33:46.111 --> 33:48.445
- [VAN DOOR OPENS]
- You saved my life.

33:48.480 --> 33:50.447
[ENGINE TURNING OVER]

33:50.482 --> 33:52.618
You saved my life.

33:53.652 --> 33:56.120
Look, if I did anything good today,

33:56.456 --> 33:57.955
it's because of you.

33:58.374 --> 34:00.049
- [VAN DOOR CLOSES]
- Let's go.

34:00.083 --> 34:01.711
Trauma team's waiting.

34:03.362 --> 34:04.795
Go.

34:04.830 --> 34:09.967
<i>♪ </i>

34:10.001 --> 34:12.469
- You coming?
- [DOORS CLOSING]

34:12.504 --> 34:15.973
<i>♪ </i>

34:16.007 --> 34:18.042
So, in my professional opinion,

34:18.076 --> 34:20.811
that right there is a giant balloon

34:20.846 --> 34:23.480
full of cocaine
in Wilson Hatch's stomach.

34:23.514 --> 34:25.049
It's at least four ounces.

34:25.083 --> 34:27.384
Okay, so... so maybe there
happens to be a balloon

34:27.418 --> 34:29.320
in my stomach, but you can't
prove what's in it.

34:29.353 --> 34:31.722
It could... it could be
something perfectly legal.

34:31.755 --> 34:33.424
So let's see it.

34:33.458 --> 34:35.960
What do you mean, here?
Just now, in the...

34:35.994 --> 34:38.728
Please, man, please.

34:38.763 --> 34:39.996
I'll be disbarred.

34:40.031 --> 34:41.831
My girlfriend will leave me.

34:41.867 --> 34:43.601
My wife will leave me.

34:43.635 --> 34:45.004
Good luck.

34:45.503 --> 34:48.339
Oh, no, no, no, no.

34:48.373 --> 34:50.306
Tre, you want to play video
games when we get home?

34:50.342 --> 34:52.976
Tre, put your hat on.
Thank y'all for coming.

34:53.011 --> 34:56.013
Evie, you should come over
for dinner every Sunday.

34:56.047 --> 34:57.748
Oh, if I came over every Sunday,

34:57.782 --> 34:59.183
I would never get any work done.

34:59.217 --> 35:01.485
- [BOTH LAUGH]
- Thank you.

35:01.519 --> 35:03.621
Here.

35:03.655 --> 35:06.457
It's yours, right?

35:12.230 --> 35:16.767
<i>♪ </i>

35:16.801 --> 35:18.836
You gonna take it or what?

35:18.870 --> 35:26.110
<i>♪ </i>

35:27.372 --> 35:29.006
No.

35:29.031 --> 35:36.071
<i>♪ </i>

35:41.526 --> 35:44.495
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

35:44.529 --> 35:51.802
<i>♪ </i>

35:53.939 --> 35:55.908
She's great.

35:55.933 --> 35:58.902
[SIGHS]

35:59.444 --> 36:01.455
Is that her?

36:04.783 --> 36:06.417
Hey.

36:06.451 --> 36:11.422
<i>♪ </i>

36:11.456 --> 36:13.257
You did it.

36:13.291 --> 36:17.096
There's somebody
who is dying to meet you.

36:17.963 --> 36:20.898
Luna, say hi to your mom.

36:20.932 --> 36:22.977
Oh, my God.

36:23.802 --> 36:25.479
Hi.

36:26.471 --> 36:28.149
Honey, you did it.

36:28.553 --> 36:30.353
[SMOOCHES]

36:30.378 --> 36:33.346
[SNIFFLES] She's perfect.

36:33.645 --> 36:35.679
Yeah.

36:35.714 --> 36:37.725
There she is.

36:37.760 --> 36:45.923
<i>♪ </i>

36:54.951 --> 36:57.720
Your mom is drop-dead gorgeous.

36:58.220 --> 37:01.456
I hope I look half as good at her age.

37:03.733 --> 37:05.467
Now is when you say,

37:05.492 --> 37:08.461
"You'll look gorgeous at any age, babe."

37:09.873 --> 37:13.176
I'm, uh... I'm sorry. I just...

37:13.210 --> 37:14.344
What's up? You haven't said

37:14.378 --> 37:16.579
more than two words since we left.

37:16.614 --> 37:18.783
Couldn't have been that bad.

37:19.216 --> 37:22.036
I couldn't have been that bad.

37:25.189 --> 37:27.690
You know, my whole life I, uh, imagined

37:27.725 --> 37:29.125
what my future would look like,

37:29.159 --> 37:30.860
what my family would look like.

37:30.894 --> 37:32.695
I had a plan.

37:32.730 --> 37:35.198
And to be honest...

37:35.232 --> 37:37.500
you don't fit into it.

37:37.534 --> 37:40.637
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

37:40.671 --> 37:42.193
So I, uh...

37:42.218 --> 37:44.107
[SIGHS]

37:44.141 --> 37:45.701
I don't know what to do.

37:46.176 --> 37:47.710
[SNIFFLES]

37:47.735 --> 37:50.137
For the first time...

37:51.802 --> 37:54.670
[GRUNTS] I, uh...

37:54.695 --> 37:56.897
I don't know what's next,

37:56.922 --> 37:59.457
and I don't care.

37:59.949 --> 38:02.125
As long as you're there,

38:02.159 --> 38:04.894
as long as you're right there with me,

38:04.928 --> 38:07.030
I don't need a plan.

38:07.064 --> 38:11.701
<i>♪ </i>

38:11.735 --> 38:13.803
Look, I don't have
your family's blessing,

38:13.837 --> 38:15.405
and I don't have mine.

38:15.439 --> 38:18.596
I don't have a ring,
I don't... I don't have anything.

38:18.631 --> 38:24.647
<i>♪ </i>

38:24.682 --> 38:26.983
Will you please,

38:27.017 --> 38:31.521
please say you'll spend
your life with me...

38:32.850 --> 38:34.884
Make a family with me...

38:35.359 --> 38:37.927
you'll marry me?

38:37.961 --> 38:43.700
<i>♪ </i>

38:43.734 --> 38:44.934
Yes.

38:44.968 --> 38:46.736
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

38:46.770 --> 38:48.571
Yes.

38:48.605 --> 38:54.777
<i>♪ </i>

38:54.812 --> 38:57.613
[LAUGHING]

38:57.648 --> 39:00.083
<i>♪ </i>

39:00.117 --> 39:02.418
[DOOR OPENS]

39:06.557 --> 39:07.890
Here you go.

39:07.925 --> 39:09.559
Thanks.

39:10.761 --> 39:12.929
So are you back down on earth yet?

39:12.963 --> 39:14.648
Yeah.

39:15.132 --> 39:17.967
First time on ecstasy
I haven't called an ex.

39:18.001 --> 39:19.135
Jacob.

39:19.169 --> 39:22.205
A joke, all right man.

39:25.008 --> 39:27.143
So why would my brain do that?

39:27.578 --> 39:29.812
That guy saved my life.

39:29.847 --> 39:32.381
Wouldn't I want to remember that?

39:33.617 --> 39:36.086
It does seem counterintuitive...

39:37.087 --> 39:40.089
until you realize how the brain works.

39:40.124 --> 39:42.325
The brain is just...

39:42.359 --> 39:45.595
it's just trying to make sense of things.

39:45.629 --> 39:49.600
Like, sometimes the world
is so beautiful, you know?

39:50.726 --> 39:52.812
<i>The laughter of a friend...</i>

39:54.021 --> 39:57.006
<i>a newborn baby gripping your finger.</i>

39:57.040 --> 39:58.841
<i>[LIGHT MUSIC]</i>

39:58.876 --> 40:01.028
<i>Life is also fragile.</i>

40:02.546 --> 40:06.649
<i>You blink, it's gone, just like that.</i>

40:06.683 --> 40:09.652
<i>[INTENSE MUSIC]</i>

40:09.686 --> 40:14.657
<i>♪ </i>

40:19.897 --> 40:22.999
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

40:23.033 --> 40:24.867
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

40:24.902 --> 40:28.671
<i>In the face of horror,
our minds turn our trauma</i>

40:28.705 --> 40:32.208
<i>into a story to make sense of it,</i>

40:32.242 --> 40:34.110
<i>even if it doesn't make sense.</i>

40:34.144 --> 40:41.417
<i>♪ </i>

40:48.192 --> 40:50.026
[SIRENS APPROACHING]

40:50.060 --> 40:53.747
<i>So why would your mind tell
you that the world was evil?</i>

40:54.531 --> 40:58.734
<i>Because evil means
that your fear is right.</i>

40:58.769 --> 41:01.704
<i>♪ </i>

41:01.738 --> 41:04.574
<i>Evil means that you can just give up.</i>

41:04.608 --> 41:06.809
<i>♪ </i>

41:06.844 --> 41:09.812
[BABY CRYING]

41:09.847 --> 41:12.882
[SIRENS APPROACHING]

41:15.285 --> 41:18.020
[NO AUDIO]

41:18.055 --> 41:25.328
<i>♪ </i>

41:30.467 --> 41:33.269
<i>But to believe that we all have</i>

41:33.303 --> 41:35.623
<i>the capacity to be heroes...</i>

41:36.473 --> 41:39.627
<i>no matter how evil the world may seem...</i>

41:40.711 --> 41:42.912
<i>that's harder...</i>

41:42.946 --> 41:46.759
<i>because that means,
when the worst happens...</i>

41:47.751 --> 41:50.853
<i>we can choose to stand up,</i>

41:50.888 --> 41:52.288
<i>we can choose to help.</i>

41:52.322 --> 41:54.123
<i>♪ </i>

41:54.157 --> 41:58.895
<i>And that's what, all day,
all around us, people do.</i>

41:59.963 --> 42:02.932
<i>So is the world dark?</i>

42:03.525 --> 42:05.225
<i>Sure.</i>

42:05.469 --> 42:07.403
<i>But there's light.</i>

42:08.572 --> 42:10.282
<i>There's so much light.</i>

42:11.475 --> 42:14.453
<i>You just have to open your eyes and look.</i>

